  "lattice_independence_proof_sketch": "For rectangular Bravais L = diag(a_t, a_x, a_y, a_z), BZ corners at L=2 minimal block are k_mu = n_mu pi / a_mu with n_mu in {0,1}. Then k_mu a_mu = n_mu pi, so 1 - cos(k_mu a_mu) = 1 - cos(n_mu pi) = 2 n_mu, independent of a_mu. The staircase depends only on the F_2^4 quotient (n_mu mod 2).",
  "exact_arithmetic_method": "sympy.cos(0)=1 and sympy.cos(pi)=-1 are exact symbolic; the Wilson sum reduces to the integer 2*hw(n) for every n in {0,1}^4.",
